19 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md` | AR-030 proposal: establishes the baseline Helm chart structure that AR-031 builds upon. |\n| 20 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/design.md` | AR-030 design: detailed Helm chart design including original RBAC structure. |\n| 21 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md` | AR-030 delta spec: original RBAC requirements before AR-031 consolidation. |\n| 22 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md` | AR-030 tasks: includes original RBAC tasks (T-007 through T-009). |\n\n---\n\n## COMPLETED vs DEFERRED ANALYSIS\n\n### COMPLETED (Implementation is in place):\n\nBased on comparing the AR-031 tasks.md checklist against actual file contents, the following AR-031 tasks **appear to be implemented** despite the checkboxes being unchecked:\n\n- **T-001 (values.yaml)**: All three RBAC keys exist in `values.yaml` with correct values.\n- **T-002 (_helpers.tpl)**: Both `agentcube.rbacName` and `agentcube.rbacBindingName` helpers are defined.\n- **T-003 (WorkloadManager RBAC)**: Template has values gate, renamed ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding, standard labels, 13 rules preserved.\n- **T-004 (Router RBAC)**: Template migrated to `rbac/router.yaml`, fixed Role/RoleBinding names, standard labels.\n- **T-005 (Delete old Router RBAC)**: `rbac-router.yaml` does NOT exist at templates root (confirmed deleted/moved).\n- **T-006 (Volcano Scheduler RBAC)**: Extracted to `rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml`, renamed ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding, standard labels, 18 rules preserved.\n- **T-007 (Volcano main template strip)**: `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` contains only ConfigMap + Service + Deployment.\n- **T-009 (Default rendering)**: Default renders 1 ClusterRole, 1 ClusterRoleBinding, 1 ServiceAccount (verified by test_render.sh).\n- **T-012 (Label consistency)**: All RBAC resources have `app.kubernetes.io/name`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`.\n- **T-016 (Directory structure)**: `templates/rbac/` contains all three files.\n\n### DEFERRED / OUT OF SCOPE (explicitly documented):\n\nFrom `changes/AR-031/proposal.md` (lines 29-34) and `design.md` (lines 680-688):\n\n| Item | Status | Details |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| **agentd RBAC** | Deferred to future AR | agentd (idle cleanup controller) needs independent SA/Role/RoleBinding following AR-031 naming conventions |\n| **picod RBAC** | Deferred to future AR | picod (sandbox execution daemon) needs independent SA/Role following AR-031 naming conventions |\n| **NetworkPolicy** | Deferred to future AR | NetworkPolicy resources for each component to limit pod-to-pod communication |\n| **PodSecurityStandards** | Deferred to future AR | Namespace-level Pod Security Standards labels (restricted/baseline/privileged) |\n| **OPA/Gatekeeper** | Independent | External policy engine integration for RBAC least-privilege validation |\n| **Kyverno** | Independent | External policy engine for automated RBAC validation and remediation |\n| **Helm RBAC unit tests** | Deferred to future AR | Introduce helm-unittest plugin to automate delta-spec scenarios |\n| **RBAC permission audit tool** | Deferred to future AR | Automated comparison of before/after permission rulesets |\n| **RBAC permission changes** | Out of scope | No apiGroups/resources/verbs are added, removed, or modified |\n\n### STATUS SUMMARY:\n\nThe AR-031 proposal.md shows all status checkboxes as unchecked:\n```\n- [ ] Proposal review\n- [ ] Implementation\n- [ ] Verification\n```\n\nHowever, the **actual implementation files** (`rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`, `rbac/router.yaml`, `rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml`, `_helpers.tpl`, `values.yaml`, and `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`) all reflect the completed state described in AR-031's design document. The tasks.md checkboxes appear to be stale -- the code matches the specification.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285a077bfffeOuGLyiStMbHPjP","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find AR-031 RBAC files","time":{"start":1775874574398,"end":1775874739219}}}}
